<HEADLINE>
<P>
FAIRPLEX; STAKES RECORD SET BY FLORES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRED ROBLEDO, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The David Flores show continued at Fairplex Park, where the five-time riding 
champion again put his name into the history book with a victorious ride on 
Shes A Sure Bet in the $50,000 Bangles And Beads Stakes Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The one-length victory over Klassy Kim was Flores' third of the day and his 
third stakes victory of the 19-day meeting, making him the all-time leading 
stakes rider at this track with 35.Francisco Mena has 34. 
</P>
<P>
 Flores, well on his way to his sixth consecutive title, now has 29 victories 
and a lead of nine over Fernando Valenzuela. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the riders in Monday's 6 1/2-furlong feature was Corey Black, a 
four-time riding champion himself. Black, who shared the title with Flores and 
Martin Pedroza in 1989, the last year he rode regularly at Fairplex, was making 
his first appearance at this meeting and had the mount on Tour. 
</P>
<P>
 Tour had one other thing going for him. He is trained by Dick Mandella, who 
had won this stakes three years in a row. 
</P>
<P>
 But this year and this day belonged to Flores. 
</P>
<P>
 Horse Racing Notes 
</P>
<P>
 Jockey Guillermo Gutierrez was thrown from his mount, Tizcomo, during the 
stretch run of the 13th race. Gutierrez, who wasn't injured, fell when Tizcomo 
stumbled, but the horse never went down. . . . Memo is drawn on the rail for 
today's $50,000 Governor's Cup at 6 1/2 furlongs. The field: Memo, Paul 
Atkinson, 124; Westcot, Antonio Castanon, 114; Ke Express, Fernando Valenzuela, 
115; Davey Be Good, David Flores, 116; Sharp Bandit, Martin Pedroza, 114. 
</P>
</TEXT>
