<P>
WHAT'S THE DEAL: BODY WATCH; HOW TO KEEP COOL WHEN THE SANTA ANA WINDS HIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CANDACE WEDLAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 We could be in for more hot spells courtesy of Santa Ana winds.Here's how to 
stay cool: 
</P>
<P>
 * Winter Park, Colo., for one week (air fare and hotel) -- about $600. 
</P>
<P>
 * Skinny-dipping at the beach -- if you get caught, fine of $250. 
</P>
<P>
 * Personal, portable fan, Hammacher Schlemmer, Beverly Hills -- $24.95. 
</P>
<P>
 * Movies, double feature at Mann Theatres -- $6.75 (before 6 p.m., $4.50). 
</P>
<P>
 * Block of ice, 25 pounds, 10-inch diameter -- Anderson Ice, Los Angeles, $2. 
</P>
<P>
 * Air-conditioned home -- 50 cents per hour. 
</P>
<P>
 * "Ice Palace" -- L.A. Public Library reading room, no charge. CANDACE WEDLAN 
