<P>
 Parents, teachers and other Ventura residents who are raising funds to build a 
community playground at Blanche Reynolds Elementary School in mid-town Ventura 
have scheduled a benefit children's concert Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The concert will feature entertainer Lori Richards, who performs regularly at 
schools, community festivals and other Southern California events. 
</P>
<P>
 A trained music educator, Richards has released records with songs such as 
"Mean Mean Babysitter" and "Dinosaurus Chorus." Her performances include 
sing-alongs with her young audiences. 
</P>
<P>
 The concert will cost $7 per person and all proceeds will go toward the 
playground. It will be held at 4 p.m. at the Ventura Theatre. 
</P>
