<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: COUNCIL OKS 700 NEW HOMES, CEMETERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A plan to build 700 dwellings, a cemetery and a public park on the Douglas 
Ranch in east Simi Valley was approved unanimously Monday by the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
 The cemetery will cover 162 acres of a 381-acre site north of the Simi Valley 
Freeway between Yosemite Avenue and Kuehner Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Other areas of the parcel will be divided between park and open space areas, 
houses, and moderate- to high-density apartments. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley council members tinkered with the number of units being proposed 
for a corner of the parcel that faced the freeway, settling on a higher-density 
project. Otherwise, they left the development blueprints unchanged. 
</P>
<P>
 The site is one of only two remaining areas in the city earmarked for a 
cemetery. An undeveloped parcel near Madera Road is also set aside for a 
cemetery, city officials said. MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
