<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; WOODBRIDGE TOPS DANA HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Yuka Suzuki and Brooke Stevens swept their sets at No. 1 doubles, helping 
Woodbridge, the fourth-ranked girls' tennis team in Orange County, beat No. 3 
Dana Hills, 14-4, in a nonleague match Monday at Woodbridge. 
</P>
<P>
 The pair won, 7-5, 6-0, 6-3.Ali Tenerelli and Julie Barraco also swept, 7-6, 
6-4, 6-2, for Woodbridge (7-1). Dana Hills is 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
 In another nonleague girls' tennis match: 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 11, Mater Dei 7 -- Nina Vaughan led 10th-ranked Corona del Mar 
(4-2) over No. 9 Mater Dei (2-3), sweeping her sets, 5-3, 6-0, 6-0. Vaughan 
defeated the Monarchs' No. 1 singles player, Laura Ruben, 5-3, in a default. 
Ruben, who was undefeated in regular-season matches last year, won her final 
sets, 6-0, 6-1. 
