</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gov. Pete Wilson has appointed Velma Montoya and Tom Sayles of Los Angeles and 
David S. Lee of Los Altos Hills to the University of California Board of 
Regents. 
</P>
<P>
 Montoya, 56, is a former associate professor of finance at Cal Poly Pomona and 
adjunct professor at the Pepperdine University School of Business. She is 
currently a member of the U.S. Occupational Safety and Health Review 
Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 Sayles, 43, is vice president of public affairs for Southern California Gas 
Co. and was formerly Wilson's Cabinet secretary for the Transportation and 
Housing Agency and served as Wilson's commissioner of corporations. 
</P>
<P>
 Lee, 57, is chairman of the board of Cortelco Systems Holding Corp. Regents 
require state Senate confirmation. The posts are unpaid. 
</P>
