GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; HEARING ON AIRPORT TERMINAL POSTPONED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A court hearing on Burbank Airport's plans to build a new, larger terminal has 
been postponed until Nov. 28 to give airport officials more time to prepare, an 
attorney said. 
</P>
<P>
 Airport officials are under a Superior Court judge's orders to redo work on an 
environmental report that concludes the terminal will not significantly 
increase noise in the area. 
</P>
<P>
 The airport's governing board has until Oct. 31 to approve an updated 
environmental study before it is presented to the judge, said Deputy City Atty. 
Keith Pritsker. VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
