PEOPLE: OGLESBY PROMOTED TO CEO OF AREA NEWSPAPER GROUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Roger Oglesby has been promoted to the new position of president and chief 
executive of California Community News Corp., a subsidiary of Los Angeles-based 
Times Mirror Co. 
</P>
<P>
 California Community News publishes the Daily Pilot, Huntington Beach 
Independent, Orange Independent and Saddleback Valley Voice in Orange County.In 
Los Angeles County, CCN publishes the Glendale News Press, the Burbank Leader 
and the Foothill Leader. 
</P>
<P>
 Times Mirror, which also owns the Los Angeles Times, acquired the CCN papers 
in May, 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 Oglesby, 46, will oversee CCN's business and editorial operations. He is a 
former Times Mirror assistant general counsel and has been assistant to the 
publisher of the Los Angeles Times since 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 Oglesby assumes his new position immediately and also continues to serve as 
assistant to Times publisher Richard T. Schlosberg. 
</P>
<P>
 "Roger Oglesby is a talented newspaper executive with considerable experience 
in both the editorial and the business arenas," Schlosberg said in a statement. 
"Under his leadership, I am confident that CCN will further strengthen Times 
Mirror's ability to provide highly localized community news and advertising to 
these important competitive markets." 
</P>
<P>
 Oglesby has held a variety of editorial positions, including assistant city 
editor at The Times, city editor for the San Jose Mercury News, metro editor at 
the Omaha World Herald and legal affairs and projects editor at the Dallas 
Times Herald. 
</P>
