<P>
 Oxy in $700-Million Oil Deal with Qatar: Los Angeles-based Occidental 
Petroleum Corp. announced that it will invest the money over 25 years in a 
production-sharing agreement to improve the Idd el Shargi North Dome Field and 
other oil fields in the Persian Gulf nation. Occidental will increase 
production using horizontal drilling and other advanced technologies. It has 
similar enhanced oil-recovery projects in Russia and Venezuela. 
