<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: REXON COLORADO CENTER REPLACES IRVINE FACILITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rexon Inc., a Simi Valley-based producer of software and computer data-storage 
systems, said it has opened an engineering center in Longmont, Colo. for its 
Wangtek and WangDAT tape-drive products. 
</P>
<P>
 The Colorado center will replace the company's Irvine facility, which is 
scheduled to be closed early next month.The move is part of a broad 
restructuring effort launched by Rexon last year, when the company reported a 
loss of $53 million amid fierce pricing competition. 
</P>
<P>
 The Irvine facility employed about 60 workers a year ago, the company said. 
About a third of the employees were transferred to Simi Valley; another third 
-- mostly engineers -- have accepted positions at the new Colorado facility. 
The remaining third were laid off or left voluntarily, the company said. 
</P>
