<TEXT>
<P>
 Security Environmental Systems Inc.: The firm said Monday that it expects to 
report a sizable loss for its fiscal year, and that it will seek a second delay 
in filing a required annual report on its financial condition with federal 
regulators. 
</P>
<P>
 The hazardous waste disposal company, based in Huntington Beach, would not say 
how much it expected to lose, but said that it needs more time to prepare its 
annual report to the Securities and Exchange Commission because of recent 
changes in management and auditors. 
</P>
<P>
 Security Environmental also said Monday that it was awarded a contract to 
dispose of hazardous waste at military installations in the Jacksonville, Fla., 
area. The contract is valued at $7.6 million. 
</P>
