<P>
 Koll Co.: A fund affiliated with the Newport Beach developer has agreed to buy 
MIP Properties Inc., the Santa Monica real estate investment trust, the company 
said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the terms of the letter of intent, a fund affiliated with Koll Co. unit 
K/B Advisors will buy 9.17 million shares of MIP's outstanding stock at $2.52 
apiece. That would put the value of the deal at about $23 million. 
</P>
<P>
 MIP Properties, formerly Mortgage Investments Plus Inc., is a real estate 
investment trust that owns office, retail and industrial properties in 
California. 
