<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; GANADO DRIVE IS RENAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There won't be two streets bearing the name of Ganado anymore. 
</P>
<P>
 That's because the Ganado with a "Drive" affixed to it is being changed to 
Calle Arroyo. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council approved the name change last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Only six residences will be affected by the switch for the 300-foot-long 
street between La Novia Avenue and Moonglow Lane. 
</P>
<P>
 The name change was prompted by some Ganado Drive residents' complaints that 
emergency personnel had trouble finding an address there because the city also 
has a Ganado Road. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
