<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; SEMINAR TO FOCUS ON PROCESS OF GRIEVING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Enhancing Our Understanding of Grief," a seminar presented by Children's 
Hospital ofOrange County and Fairhaven Memorial Park and Mortuary in Santa Ana, 
will be held from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. Thursday at the Hyatt Regency Irvine, 17900 
Jamboree Road. 
</P>
<P>
 The speaker will be Alan D. Wolfelt, director of the Colorado-based Center for 
Loss and Life Transition. 
</P>
<P>
 Topics will include the experience of grief, relating to bereaved family 
members, , and cultural rituals and traditions surrounding grief. 
</P>
<P>
 Cost of the seminar is $95, which includes lunch and materials. 
</P>
<P>
 Proceeds will support Children's Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 To register, call (800) 653-2287. ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
