<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SANTA ANA; PROSTITUTION STING NETS 48 ARRESTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police announced Monday that they had arrested 48 people in a prostitution 
sting operation. 
</P>
<P>
 The undercover operation Friday night targeted men soliciting sex along a 
four-block stretch of East 1st Street, the site of numerous resident complaints 
about prostitution, said Santa Ana police Sgt. Ed Andrade. 
</P>
<P>
 Five female officers posed as prostitutes during the seven-hour operation. Men 
were arrested when they drove up and offered to pay for sex, Andrade said. They 
were being held at the city's jail facility on suspicion of soliciting 
prostitution and had their cars impounded, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The sweep in Santa Ana follows recent anti-prostitution operations in Costa 
Mesa and Anaheim.KEN ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
</TEXT>
