COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: FULLERTON; STORY TIME OFFERED FOR TODDLERS, PARENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two-year-old children and their parents are being invited to participate in 
Fullerton Main Library's "Toddler 2x2" story time that begins Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The program, which emphasizes parent-child sharing of stories, songs and 
rhymes, will be offered on Wednesdays at 10:15 a.m. through Oct. 18 and again 
beginning Nov. 9 through Nov. 30. 
</P>
<P>
 Parents will be given lists of recommended children's books and tips on how to 
interest youngsters in reading. 
</P>
<P>
 To register for the free program, call (714) 738-6338 or pick up registration 
materials at the Children's Room in the library, at 353 W. Commonwealth Ave. 
MIMI KO 
