COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: PLACENTIA; DOCENTS SOUGHT FOR BRADFORD HOUSE TOURS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Placentia Founders Society is seeking docents to lead tours and answer 
questions about the historic Bradford House. 
</P>
<P>
 Training sessions are scheduled at 4 and 7 p.m. today for volunteers who want 
to learn the history of the house on an hourlong tour so they may teach it to 
others. 
</P>
<P>
 Volunteer docents may also join in to brush up on their knowledge. 
</P>
<P>
 Coffee will be served and soft drinks and baked goods will be available for 
purchase, with proceeds benefiting the society. An open house for docents is 
scheduled for Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 For reservations or more information, call the society at (714) 993-2470. 
