<P>
 Security forces Monday killed a Muslim extremist with a $70,000 price on his 
head, the leader of a faction that has claimed responsibility for slaying 60 
foreigners in the last year. 
</P>
<P>
 A government communique said Cherif Gousmi, 26, was slain in a gun battle in 
the Algiers region, but it gave no details. His deputy, Abdessalam Djemaoune, 
